@startuml fig-dhcp-dora
skinparam backgroundColor white
skinparam defaultFontName Arial
skinparam defaultFontSize 11
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam sequenceMessageAlign center

title DHCP: DORA — Four-Step Address Allocation

participant "Client\n(no IP yet)" as C #FFE0B2
participant "DHCP Server\n(e.g. 10.0.0.1)" as S #C8E6C9

C -[#1565C0]> S : **Discover** (broadcast)\nUDP src 0.0.0.0:68 → 255.255.255.255:67

S -[#43A047]> C : **Offer**\nProposed IP, mask, gateway, DNS, lease

C -[#1565C0]> S : **Request** (broadcast)\nAccepts the offered IP

S -[#43A047]> C : **Acknowledge**\nLease confirmed, parameters finalised

== Client now has a valid IP configuration ==

|||

C -> S : Renew (unicast at T1 = 50% lease)
S --> C : ACK (lease extended)

legend right
  D — Discover: client searches for servers
  O — Offer: server proposes an address
  R — Request: client accepts (broadcast)
  A — Acknowledge: server confirms the lease
  Renewal occurs at half the lease time
endlegend
@enduml
